-- Gap E3: a Float-param lambda passed to a higher-order fn.  The native emitter
-- now per-param infers `y : Float` from the body literal `y + 1.0` (inferParamTys/
-- paramUseTy), so the lambda body emits float arithmetic instead of integer ops on
-- the boxed-Float word.  Before the fix this printed garbage (e.g. 7.5e+168).
apply : (Float -> Float) -> Float -> Float
apply f x = f x
main : <IO> Unit
main = println (floatToString (apply (y => y + 1.0) 3.0))
